From: lophophora <lsdphophora@proton.me>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH] dateMenu: Fix zero-length events showing "7:00 - 7:00"

The comparison `eventStart === eventEnd` compares Date object references,
which is always false for two separately created Date objects, even when
they represent the same time instant. Use `getTime()` value comparison
so zero-length events display as "7:00" instead of "7:00 - 7:00".

 js/ui/dateMenu.js | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/js/ui/dateMenu.js b/js/ui/dateMenu.js
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/js/ui/dateMenu.js
+++ b/js/ui/dateMenu.js
@@ -147,7 +147,7 @@
             else
                 title = `${startDateOnly} ${startTimeOnly} ${EN_CHAR} ${endDateOnly} ${endTimeOnly}`;
-        } else if (eventStart === eventEnd) {
+        } else if (eventStart.getTime() === eventEnd.getTime()) {
             title = startTimeOnly;
         } else {
